Cook book example:
The verbal commands of the recipe, in other words, draw their meaning not from their attachment to mental representations in my head, but from their positioning within the familiar context of my activity in the home. Like signposts in a landscape, they provide specific directions to practitioners as they make their way through a field of related practices - or what I have elsewhere called a 'taskscape' (Ingold 1993b: 158).

