Whereas these authors have underlined the importance of being able to keep self and other separate, Over's paper raises the question of whether this is always opti- mal in social interaction. Instead, it may be that under certain circumstances we need to experience less of a distinction between ourselves and our social group, in order to feel a sense of belonging to that group [18].

