“At that time people in my group seemed very interesting to me,” 

as well as the behavioral level, with the following items:
“I felt more willing to do something for a group member,” and 
“I felt more committed to the way of thinking and acting of my group.” 

to test the idea that when in the flow state individuals tend to forget about themselves 
Loss of self-consciousness (three items) was used. 
One item was taken from the short version of the Flow State Scale (Garc{\'{i}}a Calvo et al., 2008): “I felt totally absorbed by what I was doing and lost consciousness of myself,” and another one “I was not worried about the image I gave to others” were used by taking into account the aspect of loss of public self-awareness, disinhibition, and loss of self-image concerns

