the feeling of fusion with the environment or with the group (Csikszentmihalyi, 1990): “I felt transported out of me and part of the group.” These three items were cre- ated to operationalize the idea that the loss of self-consciousness when in flow during group activities is not only experiencing a mere lack of public awareness of the self but also the actual merging of the self with the collective.

