Regarding emotional complementarity, 2) high-power individuals would feel less compassion than low-power individuals in response to their partner's distress.

In addition, we explored whether power affects autonomic emotion regulation as reflected in respiratory sinus arrhythmia (RSA) reactivity, an index of the neural regulation of the heart rate via the vagus nerve (Porges, Doussard-Roosevelt, {\&} Maiti, 1994).

