relative to a comparison group, women who were in- structed to regulate their emotions during a conversation about a negative film showed increased RSA during the conversation (Butler, Wilhelm, {\&} Gross, 2006)

More generally, self-regula- tory efforts, such as denying oneself a cookie or persisting at a tedious mental task, are accompanied by increased vagal control of the heart (Segerstrom {\&} Solberg Nes, 2007)

