for example, many social movements manifest threshold phenomena such that the addition or removal of the Nth individual may result in a qualitative change in the system, even though individuals N-1 and before did not.
4. Fourth, there are no cooperative or inhibitory interactions among the parts; thus, the relation between parts and whole is linear (Bechtel and Richardson 1993, 266)
