to maintain confidence when meeting with misfortunes. Children are expected to endure and overcome difficulties and chal- lenges before they become mature and successful in reaching their life goals. Two metaphors, ‘a bamboo shoot's becoming a bamboo' and ‘a fish's becoming a dragon', refer to maturity and success in the development of a strong will. Grit, 

