Distraction is an effective emotion regulation strategy (Gross, 1998) and pain fulfills this function very effectively.

Nock (2010a, 2010b), physical pain associated with self-harm serves as a distrac- tion from emotionally distressing thoughts and feelings, thereby reducing the tendency to ruminate on these mental states

