ical interest in virtue and the good life demon- strates a waxing interest in these topics. Unfor- tunately, the vast majority of authors in this emerging literature in psychology has only a rudimentary and fragmented understanding of the rich theory available on virtue and the good life (Fowers, 2005, 2008, 2010a).


