2.DESCRIBING An enhanced capacity for noting and labeling internal experiences (feelings, images, and thoughts;
3. acting with AWARENESS: An enhanced capacity for acting with present-centered awareness rather than on “automatic pilot”—lost in the past or the future
4. NON- JUDGEMENT: An enhanced ability to take a non-evaluative, non-judgmental stance toward inner thoughts, images, and feelings and outer experiences 
5. NON-REACTIVITY: An enhanced ability to allow thoughts, images, and feelings to come and go without reacting to them or getting carried away by them (5).








Self-report scales are inconclusive, and many issues associatede with them are as yet unresolved (5).







