test the social brain hypothesis on non-primate species (Shultz and Dunbar 2007; Dunbar and Shultz 2007b) have shown that, across a wide range of bird and mammal species (specifically carnivores, ungulates and bats), the social brain hypothesis takes a qualitative rather than a quantitative form. In all these taxonomic groups

